additional_house_rules: - No shoes in the house please
description: My place is two blocks from The Brooklyn Bridge Promenade and Park, walking distance to great coffee shops, cafes, and wine bars, one block to the major subway lines, and only several stops to/from Manhattan. You’ll love the location of my apartment in charming tree lined Brooklyn Heights and the warm ambiance of antiques, reclaimed/distressed furniture, antique rugs, and original art. My place is great for couples and solo adventurers.

hosts.about:
I'm a young doctor that loves arts, culture, and music. I enjoy a day exploring a city as much as a day  spent somewhere in nature hiking. 

I'm a very considerate and conscientious guest. I believe in treating someone's space with the same respect and care I would my own. I always leave a rental as clean if not cleaner than when I move in! I work long hours and enjoy quiet meditative time at home as well as meeting intelligent and engaging people.

house_rules:
• Check in time is 5PM - 7PM
• May not be safe or suitable for children (0-12 years)
• No parties or events
• Not suitable for pets
• No smoking

- No shoes in the house please
